President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in Louisiana due to the emergency conditions caused by Tropical Storm Cristobal. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. The assistance will include emergency protective measures such as evacuation and shelter support. The parishes of Acadia, Allen, Ascension, Assumption, and others will receive direct federal assistance and reimbursement for mass care. Additional parishes will receive direct federal assistance for emergency protective measures. John E. Long has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.